      "description": "Two bugs causing Boris/RTX to disappear after every RCC restart:\n\n**Bug 1 — Token amnesia:** AUTH_TOKENS is built only from RCC_AUTH_TOKENS env var at startup. Agent tokens issued via /api/agents/register are added to AUTH_TOKENS in memory but never persisted back to the env file or reloaded on restart. After restart their tokens 401 → agents appear dead.\n\n**Bug 2 — agents.json not persisting:** agents.json is currently [] — registrations are not surviving between service restarts (likely a write path bug or path mismatch with the .rcc/workspace symlink that was fixed tonight).\n\n**Fix:**\n1. On RCC startup: read agents.json and add all stored agent tokens to AUTH_TOKENS\n2. Verify agents.json write path works correctly after symlink fix\n3. For Boris and RTX: issue static tokens, add to RCC_AUTH_TOKENS in /home/jkh/.rcc/.env (same as Rocky's token) — containerized agents should use static tokens, not dynamically-generated ones that die on restart\n4. Document the token issuance process in ONBOARDING.md\n\n**Why this keeps happening:** Boris and RTX have onboarded 5+ times. Each time RCC restarts they lose their tokens. Static env-var tokens are the correct permanent solution for containerized agents.",
