      "status": "blocked",
      "title": "Container agent first-class presence: OpenClaw polling mode + memory sync",
      "description": "L40 Sweden containers (Peabody, Boris, Sherman, Snidely, Dudley) should be first-class agents with SquirrelBus + work queue participation, not just dumb vLLM endpoints.\n\n## What they need\n1. **OpenClaw in supervisord** — `[program:openclaw-gateway]` conf, poll-only mode (no inbound port needed)\n2. **Poll interval tuning** — work queue poll every 30s is fine; heartbeat every 60s; SquirrelBus subscription via outbound SSE (no inbound)\n3. **Memory persistence** — MEMORY.md + memory/*.md synced to MinIO on session end, pulled on start. Containers lose local disk on restart — MinIO is the persistence layer.\n4. **Onboard script update** — for container vllm-worker role: install OpenClaw into supervisord alongside vLLM, not skip it. Write both confs in one pass.\n5. **RCC exec routing** — /api/exec currently broadcasts via SquirrelBus. Container agents will receive these if they have an active SSE subscription. Verify Boris receives and acks exec payloads.\n\n## Memory sync design\n- On openclaw session end hook: `mc cp ~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md do-host1/agents/{name}/MEMORY.md`\n- On openclaw session start: pull from MinIO if local is older than 1h\n- Daily memory files: same pattern (memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md)\n- MinIO bucket: `agents` (already configured on do-host1)\n\n## Why this matters\nThese nodes have 4x L40 GPUs, more RAM than any OpenClaw machine in the fleet, and plenty of CPU. They can take real work — code review, inference tasks, long-running analysis — not just serve tokens. Poll-only is fine for responsiveness given 30s latency is acceptable for most tasks.\n\n## Dependency\nPass 1 must complete first: vLLM tunnel up on all nodes.",
