      "title": "deploy: add container-aware setup path (supervisord, no systemd/cron)",
      "description": "During agent-rtx onboarding (2026-03-25), we discovered that the existing deploy scripts assume a full Linux host with systemd and crontab. Kasm workspace containers (and likely other container environments) break several assumptions:\n\n**What fails in containers:**\n- `crontab` not available (command not found)\n- `systemctl --user` fails — no D-Bus session (`$DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS` and `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` not set)\n- System `systemctl` fails — not booted with systemd as PID 1\n- PID 1 is `supervisord` (running from `/etc/supervisord.conf`)\n\n**What works / what we did:**\n1. Symlinked `~/.rcc/workspace` → existing repo clone (avoids duplicate checkout)\n2. Wrote `~/.rcc/rcc-pull-loop.sh` — a simple `while true; do bash agent-pull.sh; sleep 600; done` wrapper\n3. Appended a `[program:rcc-agent-pull]` block to `/etc/supervisord.conf` (requires sudo)\n4. Ran `sudo supervisorctl -c /etc/supervisord.conf reread && update` to activate\n5. Started Claude tmux session: `tmux new-session -d -s claude-main` then sent `claude --dangerously-skip-permissions` + `Down` + `Enter` (Down arrow must be sent separately before Enter for the bypass prompt)\n6. Pre-create log file as correct user to avoid root-owned file ownership issue\n\n**Goal for rocky:**\nAdd a `deploy/setup-container.sh` (or extend `setup-node.sh` with container detection) that:\n- Detects container environment: check if PID 1 is supervisord/docker-init/not systemd\n- Skips crontab/systemd steps\n- Writes the supervisord `[program:rcc-agent-pull]` snippet and reloads it\n- Starts the Claude tmux session automatically\n- Pre-creates `~/.rcc/logs/pull.log` owned by the correct user\n- Documents this in `deploy/README.md` under a \"Container Environments\" section\n\nThe loop script approach is already proven working on agent-rtx.",
