      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Wire Milvus RAG into every conversation and memory write path",
      "description": "Currently Milvus is running with rcc_lessons/rcc_queue/rcc_memory collections but nothing is actually using it for retrieval. Flat markdown files are read cold at session start.\n\nRequired:\n\n1. **Ingest pipeline** — on every write to:\n   - memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (daily log)\n   - MEMORY.md (long-term)\n   - queue items (create/complete)\n   - lessons\n   - SquirrelChat messages\n   ...embed the text and upsert into the appropriate Milvus collection.\n\n2. **RAG query helper** — rcc/vector/query.mjs: given a query string, search all relevant collections, return top-k chunks with source metadata.\n\n3. **Session bootstrap RAG** — at session start, instead of loading all of MEMORY.md, query Milvus for chunks relevant to: (a) the incoming message, (b) recent context (last 24h), (c) ongoing tasks. Inject only those chunks.\n\n4. **Conversation-level RAG** — as conversation progresses, each user turn triggers a background Milvus search; relevant past context injected as a system message if found.\n\n5. **SquirrelChat ingestion** — every message posted to SquirrelChat bus gets embedded + stored in rcc_memory collection.\n\n6. **API endpoint** — GET /api/vector/context?q=<query>&k=10 returns top-k relevant chunks across all collections for use by any agent.\n\nAudit logs (flat markdown, JSONL) stay as durable truth. Milvus is retrieval layer only.\n\nExisting infrastructure:\n- Milvus at localhost:19530\n- Embed model: azure/openai/text-embedding-3-large (3072-dim)\n- Module: rcc/vector/index.mjs\n- Collections: rcc_lessons, rcc_queue, rcc_memory",
