      "description": "jkh directive 2026-03-27: The canonical design is:\n\n- RCC is the sole holder of all secrets: GitHub deploy key, Slack app token, Mattermost credentials, Milvus address, MinIO creds, etc.\n- The ONLY thing an agent and RCC need to share is the RCC admin token (or a short-lived bootstrap token derived from it).\n- Once an agent presents that token to RCC, RCC hands it everything else it needs to operate.\n- Agents do NOT store long-lived secrets locally (except the admin/bootstrap token itself).\n\n## Audit and enforce this design:\n\n1. **Audit current state** — scan .rcc/.env on do-host1 and rockyandfriends deploy/.env.template. Identify every secret currently stored on agents that should instead be fetched from RCC.\n\n2. **RCC secret registry** — ensure RCC has endpoints for all secrets agents currently need:\n   - GET /api/secrets/github (deploy key + repo URL) ✓ (wq-RCC-bootstrap-001)\n   - GET /api/secrets/slack (bot token + signing secret)\n   - GET /api/secrets/mattermost (server URL + token per agent)\n   - GET /api/secrets/minio (endpoint + access key + secret key)\n   - GET /api/secrets/milvus (address)\n   - GET /api/secrets/nvidia (API key / inference gateway URL)\n   - Generic: GET /api/secrets/:key for arbitrary KV\n\n3. **Bootstrap flow audit** — verify deploy/bootstrap.sh + deploy/migrate.sh correctly:\n   - Accept only the admin token as input\n   - Fetch all other secrets from RCC after auth\n   - Write them to ~/.rcc/.env (not hardcoded in scripts)\n   - Never log or expose the admin token\n\n4. **Secret rotation** — when a secret is rotated in RCC, agents should be able to re-fetch on next heartbeat without re-bootstrapping. Add: POST /api/secrets/:key (admin-only write), and agent-pull.sh should call a secrets-sync step.\n\n5. **Token hierarchy clarification** — document the token model:\n   - RCC_ADMIN_TOKEN: jkh-only, stored in RCC .env, never distributed to agents\n   - RCC_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN: short-lived, single-use, generated by admin for new agent onboarding\n   - RCC_AGENT_TOKEN: long-lived per-agent token RCC returns at bootstrap, used for normal API calls\n   - All other secrets: fetched from RCC using agent token, never pre-distributed\n\n6. **DIRECTIVES.md update** — add: agents must not store secrets outside of what RCC provides. If a secret is needed and not in ~/.rcc/.env, fetch it from RCC.\n\n7. **Security model doc** — write rcc/docs/security-model.md capturing this hierarchy clearly for future agent onboarding.",
