      "title": "RCC API + Dashboard UI: comprehensive test suite from scratch",
      "description": "Both the RCC API (rcc/api/index.mjs) and the Dashboard UI (rcc/workspace/dashboard/) are new, actively broken, and have no reliable test coverage. This task is to build a comprehensive test suite from zero — do not assume any existing tests are correct or complete.\n\n## Context\n\nYou are starting from scratch. The codebase is at /home/horde/.rcc/workspace (or /home/jkh/.rcc/workspace on Rocky). The RCC API runs on port 8789. The dashboard UI is served from the same port or adjacent (check dashboard/server.mjs). Recent breakages include:\n- GET /api/bootstrap was behind the auth gate (unauthenticated agents got 401 — now fixed)\n- Bootstrap token flow was silently failing and falling through to offline mode\n- Dashboard UI has known breakage (details unknown — discover via testing)\n\n## Deliverables\n\n### 1. API test suite (tests/api/)\nWrite a Node.js test suite (no external test framework required — use node:assert + node:test, or vitest if already available). Cover:\n\n**Auth & bootstrap flow:**\n- POST /api/bootstrap/token requires admin auth — 401 without, 200 with\n- GET /api/bootstrap with valid token returns ok:true, agentToken, secrets, repoUrl, deployKey\n- GET /api/bootstrap with invalid/expired/used token returns 401\n- GET /api/bootstrap is reachable WITHOUT an agent token (critical regression test)\n- Bootstrap token is single-use (second call with same token → 401)\n\n**Heartbeat:**\n- POST /api/heartbeat/:agent accepts valid payload, returns 200\n- GET /api/agents lists registered agents\n- GET /api/agents/status shows online/offline/last-seen\n- Agent marked offline after >1h silence\n\n**Queue:**\n- GET /api/queue returns items and completed arrays\n- POST /api/queue creates item\n- PATCH /api/item/:id updates status\n- GET /api/queue requires no auth (public)\n- POST /api/queue requires auth\n\n**Secrets:**\n- GET /api/secrets/:key returns secret for authenticated agent\n- GET /api/secrets/:key returns 401 for unauthenticated request\n- POST /api/secrets/:key requires admin token\n- Named aliases (slack, nvidia, mattermost, minio, milvus) return bundle objects\n\n**Health:**\n- GET /health returns ok:true, uptime, agentCount, queueDepth\n- No auth required\n\n**Error cases:**\n- 404 for unknown routes\n- 400 for missing required params\n- 401 for auth-required routes without token\n\n### 2. UI smoke tests (tests/ui/)\nThe dashboard UI needs basic smoke tests. Use Playwright (install if needed) or a lightweight fetch-based HTML parser. Cover:\n\n- Dashboard loads at root URL (HTTP 200, content-type text/html)\n- Agent list renders (agents appear in DOM)\n- Queue section renders (queue items visible or empty state shown)\n- No JS console errors on load\n- All static assets (CSS, JS) return 200\n- Bootstrap token generation UI (if present) is functional\n\n### 3. Integration test: full bootstrap flow\nEnd-to-end test simulating what Boris/RTX would do:\n1. POST /api/bootstrap/token (admin auth) → get token\n2. GET /api/bootstrap?token=... (NO auth header) → get agentToken + secrets\n3. POST /api/heartbeat/test-agent with the new agentToken → 200\n4. GET /api/agents/status → test-agent appears\n5. Cleanup: mark test-agent decommissioned\n\n### 4. CI runner script (tests/run-tests.sh)\n- Starts a test instance of the API on a random port (or uses live instance)\n- Runs all tests\n- Exits non-zero on failure\n- Prints clear pass/fail summary\n- Safe to run on any agent (Rocky, Natasha, Boris)\n\n### 5. Document discovered bugs\nAs you write tests, you will discover things that are broken. For each bug found:\n- Note it in tests/BUGS.md\n- Create a workqueue item via POST /api/queue\n- Do NOT fix bugs in this task — only document and queue them\n\n## How to run the API locally\n```bash\n# The live RCC instance is at http://localhost:8789 (or http://146.190.134.110:8789)\n# Admin token: first token in RCC_AUTH_TOKENS from ~/.rcc/.env\n# For isolated testing, you can spawn a second instance on a different port:\nRCC_PORT=8799 node /home/horde/.rcc/workspace/rcc/api/index.mjs &\n```\n\n## Commit instructions\nWhen done:\n```bash\ngit add tests/ && git commit -m \"test(rcc): comprehensive API + UI test suite from scratch\"\ngit push origin main\n```\n\nThen PATCH this item to completed:\n```bash\ncurl -s -X PATCH http://146.190.134.110:8789/api/item/wq-TEST-rcc-001 \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer <your-agent-token>\" \\\n  -d '{\"status\":\"completed\",\"result\":\"<summary of what was written and bugs found>\"}'\n```",
