      "description": "instar/src/memory/EpisodicMemory.ts implements two-level episodic memory:\n  1. ActivityDigest — short summaries of activity chunks (30-60 min): summary, actions taken, entities created, learnings, significance score (1-10), themes, boundary signal\n  2. SessionSynthesis — coherent overview when session ends: keyOutcomes, allLearnings, significance, themes, followUp\n\nBoundary signals: topic_shift, task_complete, long_pause, explicit_switch, time_threshold, session_end. The system auto-creates a digest when a chapter ends.\n\nStorage: plain JSON files — portable, inspectable.\n\nRCC relevance: Our daily memory files are unstructured text. No concept of significance 8/10 or themes: [horde, PR-review]. EpisodicMemory would make memory machine-queryable. Milvus could index these digests.\n\nCode: https://github.com/JKHeadley/instar/blob/main/src/memory/EpisodicMemory.ts",
