      "title": "TEST SUITE: Validate all instar-derived features before RCC merge",
      "description": "BLOCKED BY: All 10 instar-scout tasks (wq-INSTAR-*-01 through wq-INSTAR-*-10).\nDo not start this task until all 10 preceding tasks are complete.\n\nWrite a comprehensive test suite covering every feature adopted or adapted from the instar scout:\n\n1. CoherenceGate (task -01)\n   - PEL hard block fires on policy violations\n   - Gate reviewer correctly bypasses full panel for clean messages\n   - Each specialist reviewer (settling, capability-accuracy, etc.) catches its canary\n   - Retry logic: block -> feedback -> revision -> pass\n   - Retry exhaustion: passes with warning after maxRetries\n   - External vs internal channel behavior differs correctly\n   - Audit log records all verdicts\n\n2. ExternalOperationGate (task -02)\n   - Risk matrix: read=low, single-delete-irreversible=high, bulk-delete=critical\n   - Blocked services return block immediately\n   - Read-only services block write/modify/delete\n   - LLM proportionality check only fires for medium+ risk\n   - Bulk operations always require plan regardless of autonomy profile\n   - Batch checkpoints inserted at correct intervals\n   - Operation log written atomically\n\n3. AdaptiveTrust (task -03)\n   - Earned trust increments on successful ops\n   - Trust revocation fires on incident\n   - Trust floor prevents auto-escalation to autonomous\n   - Granted trust (explicit user) can reach autonomous\n   - Trust profile persists across restarts\n\n4. WorkingMemoryAssembler (task -04)\n   - Token budgets respected per source\n   - Tiered rendering: top-3 full, next-7 compact, rest name-only\n   - Per-term search + merge gives OR-like recall\n   - Stop words filtered from query terms\n   - Graceful degradation when memory system unavailable\n\n5. EpisodicMemory (task -05)\n   - ActivityDigest created on each boundary signal\n   - SessionSynthesis composed on session end\n   - getRecentActivity returns correct time window\n   - getByTheme returns theme-matching digests\n   - Significance scoring influences retrieval order\n\n6. dangerous-command-guard (task -06)\n   - Always-block patterns fire regardless of safety level\n   - Level 1: risky patterns block and require user auth\n   - Level 2: risky patterns inject self-verification JSON (not block)\n   - Non-matching commands pass through\n\n7. serendipity-capture (task -07)\n   - Rate limit enforced (max N per session)\n   - Required fields validated\n   - Secret patterns rejected\n   - HMAC signature computed and stored\n   - Atomic write (tmp + rename)\n   - Patch file path traversal rejected\n\n8. IntentDriftDetector (task -08) — if implemented\n   - Conflict spike detected when conflict rate increases\n   - Confidence drop detected\n   - Principle shift detected when top principles change\n   - No drift detected on stable journals\n\n9. free-text-guard (task -09)\n   - Password/token questions blocked\n   - Decision questions (which, choose, prefer) allowed\n   - Mixed (decision + free-text) evaluated correctly\n\n10. Threadline/OpenClawBridge (task -10) — if implemented\n    - Agent identity keypair generation\n    - Handshake protocol\n    - Circuit breaker opens after N failures\n    - Rate limit enforced per agent pair\n\nTest requirements:\n  - All tests must pass on do-host1 before merge to main RCC branch\n  - Tests must be runnable via: npm test / node --test / vitest (match existing RCC test infra)\n  - Each feature must have unit tests AND at least one integration test\n  - Test output must be machine-parseable (TAP or JSON) for CI gate\n  - Add test run to rcc-api.service startup health check\n\nDefinition of done: CI green, all features tested, test report filed to RCC lessons ledger.",
