      "description": "Full design spec already exists in branch feature/dashboard-v2-geek-view (rcc/docs/dashboard-v2-design.md, section 7). Implement as part of the Rust/WASM dashboard.\n\nGeek View = SVG topology map of the entire system with live traffic animation.\n\n## What It Shows\n- **Nodes (machines primary):** Rocky (do-host1), Bullwinkle (puck), Natasha (sparky), Boris (l40-sweden), plus shared services (Milvus, MinIO, SearXNG) as standalone nodes. External services (NVIDIA Gateway, GitHub, Mattermost, Slack x2, Telegram) on the periphery.\n- **Service chips per machine:** Each agent node shows inline chips for services running on it (e.g. Rocky shows: RCC API :8789, Dashboard :8788, Brain, SquirrelBus hub, Tailscale proxy).\n- **Edges:** solid = persistent connection, dashed = on-demand call. Labels show protocol.\n- **Live traffic particles:** animated dots flow along edges on SquirrelBus events, heartbeats, brain requests.\n- **Node pulse:** pulse animation if active in last 5min. Color: 🟢 <5min, 🟡 5-30min, 🔴 >30min.\n\n## Data Sources\n- GET /api/geek/topology — node/edge map + live status (heartbeats, uptime, queue depth)\n- GET /api/geek/stream — SSE for live traffic events (already partially implemented in the branch)\n- GET /api/heartbeats — for agent status\n\n## Traffic Log Panel\nBottom panel: last 20 events with timestamp, from→to, type (heartbeat/bus_msg/brain_req).\n\n## Unanswered Message Queue\nFiltered SquirrelBus view: messages sent without response. 'Rocky → Bullwinkle: 12 unanswered' is a health signal.\n\n## Soul Commit Timeline\nPer-agent: last commit to souls/ repo dir. Show as a strip below each agent node.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- SVG preferred over Canvas (accessibility + CSS animations)\n- Static layout (hand-tuned, not force-directed) — see rough sketch in design spec\n- SSE reconnects automatically; falls back to 5s poll if SSE fails\n- Dark theme matching rest of dashboard\n- Branch feature/dashboard-v2-geek-view has par