      "title": "Branch consolidation: audit stale branches, merge or tombstone, add CI gate",
      "description": "Pattern identified 2026-03-27: task filed → branch created → task closed → branch orphaned, never merged. Main drifts from reality. Example: feature/dashboard-v2-geek-view had a full design spec and partial implementation sitting unmerged while we patched the old Node.js dashboard.\n\nThis task has two parts:\n\n## Part 1: Immediate Audit\nFor every branch in origin that isn't main/master:\n1. Check if it's ahead of main (has unmerged commits)\n2. Classify: (a) work worth merging, (b) superseded/stale, (c) in-progress with active task\n3. For (a): open a PR or merge directly\n4. For (b): delete the branch, add a tombstone note to the relevant queue item\n5. For (c): link the branch name to its queue item via a comment\n\nCurrent branches to audit:\n- feature/dashboard-v2-api\n- feature/dashboard-v2-frontend  \n- feature/dashboard-v2-geek-view\n- natasha/local-work\n- natasha/sparky-main-2026-03-27\n- natasha/merge-sparky-2026-03-27 (already merged — delete)\n\n## Part 2: Systemic Fix — Branch Lifecycle Gate\n\nAdd a cron job (Rocky, every 24h) that:\n1. Lists all remote branches not merged into main\n2. For each, checks age of last commit\n3. If >72h unmerged and no open queue item linking to it: files a new queue item flagged needsHuman=true: 'Orphaned branch X — merge or delete?'\n4. If >7d unmerged with no activity: escalates to Slack #rockyandfriends\n5. Posts a daily digest to #rockyandfriends: 'N branches ahead of main: [list]'\n\nImplementation:\n- Script: scripts/branch-audit.mjs (or .sh)\n- Cron: daily at 09:00 PT\n- Queue item scout_key: branch-orphan-<branch-name> (dedup — only one alert per branch)\n- Merge discipline: no task is 'done' until its branch is merged OR explicitly tombstoned\n\n## Part 3: Definition-of-Done Protocol\nUpdate WORKQUEUE_AGENT.md: a task that involves code changes is not complete until:\n1. Changes are committed to a branch\n2. Branch is merged to main (or PR opened)\n3. /api/item/:id/complete is called AFTER the merge, not before\n\nThis is the intrinsic motivation: the queue item stays open until main reflects the work.",
