      "title": "Task completion callbacks — notify jkh on Slack when any agent completes a task",
      "description": "When any agent calls POST /api/item/:id/complete, RCC should automatically notify jkh on Slack. Currently completions are silent — jkh only finds out by checking the dashboard.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### RCC API side (post-completion hook)\nIn the /complete handler, after writing the queue, fire a non-blocking Slack notification:\n- Channel: DM to jkh (UDYR7H4SC on omgjkh.slack.com)\n- Format: '✅ *<title>* — completed by <agent>\\n<resolution or result, truncated to 200 chars>\\n_<id>_'\n- Only for items with priority != 'idea' (skip idea promotions/closures — too noisy)\n- Only for items where assignee != 'jkh' (jkh completing his own items is obvious)\n- Fire-and-forget: completion succeeds even if Slack call fails\n\n### Config\n- SLACK_NOTIFY_TOKEN — which bot token to use (default: OMGJKH_BOT)\n- SLACK_NOTIFY_USER — jkh's user ID (UDYR7H4SC)\n- RCC reads these from secrets/env; no hardcoding\n- Opt-out: if item has tag 'silent' or 'no-notify', skip\n\n### Scope\n- POST /api/item/:id/complete (new callback endpoints) — yes\n- POST /api/complete/:id (legacy dashboard endpoint) — yes, same hook\n- PATCH /api/item/:id with status=completed — yes\n- Auto-archive of stale items (expire-stale) — no (system action, not agent completion)\n\n### Deduplication\n- Track notified item IDs in memory (Map, cleared on restart) — don't double-notify if somehow called twice\n\n## Definition of Done\n- Rocky completes a test item, jkh receives a Slack DM within 5 seconds\n- Natasha completes a GPU task, jkh receives notification\n- Idea items and jkh-assigned items do NOT generate notifications\n- RCC API restart does not cause duplicate notifications for already-completed items",
