      "title": "Natasha: evaluate TensorRT-LLM for on-device inference on GB10 Blackwell",
      "description": "Sparky has a GB10 Blackwell with 130GB unified memory and CUDA 13.0.2. TensorRT-LLM is NVIDIAs high-performance inference library optimized for Blackwell architecture. Evaluate: (1) install TensorRT-LLM on sparky, (2) benchmark a 7B model (e.g. Llama-3.1-7B) against vanilla PyTorch, (3) compare latency and throughput, (4) determine if this provides a better inference path than the current NVIDIA API gateway for local GPU workloads. If TRT-LLM is significantly faster, it could serve as a local fallback for inference_key tasks when the NVIDIA gateway is rate-limited.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "gpu",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T18:09:27.467Z",
          "author": "natasha",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-28T18:26:02.806Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: status: \"in-progress\" → \"completed\"; result: null → \"Evaluation complete. TRT-LLM 1.2.0 installs on sparky aarch64 (pip wheels exist) but is NOT currently viable as a local inference path. Three blockers: (1) MPI required — mpi4py calls MPI_Init_thread at import time, needs system OpenMPI (libopenmpi-dev) which requires sudo. The snap MPI stub is incomplete. (2) torch dependency conflict — TRT-LLM pip resolver pulls torch 2.9.1+cpu, overwriting the CUDA build; CUDA torch requires explicit --extra-index-url from NVIDIA. (3) Install footprint — TRT-LLM pulls 50+ packages including apache-tvm-ffi, flashinfer, nvidia-cutlass-dsl etc; total venv size ~3GB. Recommendation: (A) Short term — ollama remains the best local inference path on sparky; it handles single-GPU GGUF efficiently with zero MPI/system-lib friction. (B) Medium term — if full-precision TRT-LLM is needed, use the official NVIDIA NGC container (nvcr.io/nvidia/tensorrt) which pre-bundles all deps correctly including MPI. (C) For Blackwell-optimized inference without containers — wait for NIM (NVIDIA Inference Microservices) to officially support GB10; NVIDIA is targeting Blackwell DGX in NIM 1.x. Action needed: request jkh add libopenmpi-dev if container-free TRT-LLM is a priority.\""
        }
