      "id": "wq-NAT-squirrelchat-slack-clone-001",
      "itemVersion": 3,
      "created": "2026-03-29T10:46:00.568Z",
      "source": "jkh-directive",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "SquirrelChat: full Slack-replacement — channels, threads, users, file sharing, emoji reactions",
      "description": "Evolve SquirrelChat (already in rcc/dashboard as a Leptos/WASM component) into a full-featured Slack replacement. Stack stays Rust + WASM (Leptos 0.6 CSR, Axum backend). Every participant — human or agent — is just a user account; no distinction at the protocol level.\n\nFeature target (MVP for Slack replacement):\n1. **Channels** — create/join/leave channels, channel list in sidebar, public + private\n2. **Threads** — reply-in-thread on any message, thread summary in sidebar\n3. **Users** — user accounts with display name, avatar, online/away/offline presence\n4. **Direct Messages** — 1:1 and small-group DMs\n5. **Emoji reactions** — react to messages with any emoji, reaction counts + who reacted\n6. **File sharing** — upload/attach files, inline image previews, download links\n7. **Message formatting** — markdown rendering (bold, italic, code blocks, links)\n8. **Notifications** — unread badges per channel, browser/desktop notifications for mentions\n9. **@mentions** — @user and @channel mentions with highlights\n10. **Search** — full-text search across messages\n11. **Message history** — persistent storage backend (SQLite or Postgres via RCC)\n\nExplicitly NOT needed:\n- Third-party app integrations (webhooks, bots-as-apps)\n- Slack API compatibility shim\n- Separate bot accounts (agents = normal users)\n\nArchitecture notes:\n- Backend: Axum WebSocket server for real-time, REST for history/search/file upload\n- Frontend: Leptos reactive components, SSE or WebSocket for live updates\n- Storage: SQLite for messages/channels/users to start, Postgres migration path\n- Auth: simple token-based auth tied to RCC agent identity\n- File storage: local disk initially, S3-compatible later\n\nPhased delivery:\n- Phase 1: channels + persistent messages + users + presence (replaces #general usage)\n- Phase 2: threads + emoji reactions + @mentions + unread badges\n- Phase 3: DMs + file sharing + search\n- Phase 4: notifications + markdown + polish",
      "notes": "Phase 1 shipped: Axum WS server (Rocky), WASM frontend WS transport swap, EmojiPicker+ReactionsBar+ThreadPanel+CreateChannelModal (Bullwinkle), type alignment. Live on 8793+8788.",
