      "title": "[agentos] Dynamic agent spawn from init_agent",
      "description": "Currently workers are statically defined in agentos.system. Phase 2 requires init_agent to dynamically spawn new agent PDs at runtime.\n\nDesign:\n- init_agent receives SPAWN_AGENT message via MsgBus with WASM module hash\n- Fetches module from AgentFS by hash\n- Allocates a free worker slot from agent pool\n- Loads WASM into swap slot via vibe_swap mechanism\n- Grants initial CSpace capabilities (MsgBus ep, AgentFS ep, LogSvc ep)\n- Returns new agent_id to caller\n\nThis is the critical path for making agentOS actually useful as a runtime.",
