      "id": "wq-API-1774817798606",
      "itemVersion": 5,
      "created": "2026-03-29T20:56:38.606Z",
      "source": "api",
      "assignee": "rocky",
      "priority": "high",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "Revamp /api/onboard installer — full host discovery + vLLM/tailscale-aware registration",
      "description": "The current onboard script has multiple gaps discovered during Peabody/Sherman/Snidely/Dudley onboarding.\n\n---\n\n## Root problems (original)\n\n1. Bootstrap token creation stores agent record with only token+registeredAt — no name/host/capabilities (partially fixed in 4fa97dd but still not collecting GPU info at onboard time)\n2. The generated script does not auto-detect GPU count/model/VRAM and include it in registration\n3. No distinction between \"normal agent\" vs \"vLLM agent\" — role selection is a manual flag, not self-detected\n4. Tailscale detection is absent — if tailscale is running, agent can communicate directly; if not, it must SSH reverse-tunnel its vLLM port. Script always tunnels or never tunnels based on manual flag.\n5. GPU info only collected in the vllm-worker path — normal agents with GPUs are invisible to dashboard\n\n## Additional bugs found during tunnel remediation (2026-03-29)\n\n6. **authorized_keys write not verified** — RCC catches the write error silently and returns 200 anyway. Script declares tunnel registered when it was not. Fix: verify write succeeded before returning ok; script must check response confirms key on disk.\n\n7. **Bare pubkeys in authorized_keys** — Peabody key written without restrict/permitopen guards (out-of-band during failed onboard). Gives tunnel user broader SSH access than intended. Fix: /api/tunnel/request always applies restrictions; add sanitize scan at RCC startup for bare entries.\n\n8. **Agent tokens in SquirrelBus plaintext** — tunnel remediation messages included RCC_AGENT_TOKEN in payload. Fix: onboard script writes token to ~/.rcc/.env; tunnel step sources .env instead of receiving token via messaging channel.\n\n9. **No end-to-end tunnel verification** — script declares success after heartbeat POST without confirming tunnel is established, vLLM reachable, or key actually in authorized_keys. Fix: add /api/tunnel/verify endpoint; script must get green from it before printing success.\n\n10. **systemd --user needs loginctl enable-linger** — without it, tunnel and vLLM services die on logout/reboot. Fix: add `sudo loginctl enable-linger $USER` to vllm-worker setup.\n\n11. **TUNNEL_USER defaults to \"jkh\", actual tunnel user is \"tunnel\"** — /api/tunnel/request returns connect string with wrong username. Agents following it literally will fail. Fix: set TUNNEL_USER=tunnel in ~/.rcc/.env; fix the hardcoded default in index.mjs from \"jkh\" to \"tunnel\"; verify at RCC startup.\n\n---\n\n## What the revamped installer must do\n\n1. **Auto-detect** at install time: nvidia-smi (GPU count/model/VRAM), tailscale status + IP, hostname, disk space\n2. **Self-select role**: >=64GB total VRAM → vllm-worker default; GPU but <64GB → register caps, skip vLLM; no GPU → plain agent\n3. **Tailscale-aware tunnel**: tailscale present → register tailscale_ip, no SSH tunnel needed; no tailscale → SSH reverse tunnel to Rocky\n4. **Registration payload** includes: name, host, type, gpu/gpu_model/gpu_count/gpu_vram_gb, vllm/vllm_port, tailscale/tailscale_ip, claude_cli=true\n5. **/api/agents/register** stores tailscale_ip, updates LLM baseUrl to tailscale_ip:8080 or tunnel localhost port\n6. **TokenHub auto-registration** works for both paths (tunnel port OR tailscale_ip:vllm_port)\n7. **Bootstrap token** accepts optional role hint but script defaults to auto-detect\n8. **Tunnel setup atomic + verified** — write key, confirm in authorized_keys, confirm SSH handshake, confirm vLLM reachable through tunnel, THEN declare success\n9. **TUNNEL_USER=tunnel** enforced in .env and in index.mjs default\n10. **loginctl enable-linger** called for all vllm-worker installs\n\n---\n\n## Deliverables\n\n1. Updated `GET /api/onboard` — auto-detect, role self-select, tailscale-aware, verified tunnel setup\n2. Updated `POST /api/agents/register` — tailscale_ip + full GPU caps stored\n3. Set `TUNNEL_USER=tunnel` in ~/.rcc/.env; fix default in index.mjs\n4. authorized_keys sanitize/audit at RCC startup (warn on bare entries, optionally rewrite)\n5. `POST /api/tunnel/verify` — end-to-end tunnel health check endpoint\n6. Update ONBOARD_NEW_AGENT.md to reflect new flow\n7. Fix TUNNEL_USER default: `|| 'jkh'` → `|| 'tunnel'` in index.mjs\n\n## Already done — do not re-do\n\n- peabody/snidely/sherman/dudley patched with 4xL40/190GB/vllm=true in agents.json\n- Tunnel ports pre-allocated: peabody=18082, snidely=18083, sherman=18084, dudley=18085\n- authorized_keys ACL fixed so jkh process can write\n- SquirrelBus tunnel-setup messages sent to all four agents (seq 229-232)\n- agent record name/host bug fixed in onboard handler (3 locations, commit 4fa97dd)\n- Junk test agent entries cleaned from agents.json",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "claude_cli",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-29T21:03:48.985Z",
          "author": "rocky",
          "type": "claim",
          "text": "Claimed"
        },
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-29T21:08:19.323Z",
          "author": "api",
          "type": "status-change",
          "text": "Updated: description: \"The current onboard script has multiple gaps discovered during Peabody/Sherman/Snidely/Dudley onboarding:\\n\\n**Root problems:**\\n1. Bootstrap token creation stores agent record with only token+registeredAt — no name/host/capabilities (partially fixed in 4fa97dd but still not collecting GPU info at onboard time)\\n2. The generated script does not auto-detect GPU count/model/VRAM and include it in registration\\n3. No distinction between \\\"normal agent\\\" (claude/openclaw only) and \\\"vLLM agent\\\" (has local GPU, wants to run vLLM + reverse-tunnel the port to Rocky) — this role selection is currently a manual flag in the bootstrap token, not self-detected\\n4. Tailscale detection is absent — if tailscale is running on the new host, it can communicate directly; if not, it MUST set up the SSH reverse tunnel for vLLM port forwarding. Currently the script always tries the tunnel regardless.\\n5. GPU info (model, count, VRAM) is only collected in the vllm-worker path — normal agents with GPUs are invisible to the dashboard\\n\\n**What the revamped installer must do:**\\n1. **Auto-detect at install time:**\\n   - `nvidia-smi` → GPU count, model, VRAM per card (sum VRAM)\\n   - `tailscale status` → is tailscale running? capture tailscale IP\\n   - hostname, OS, available disk space for model storage\\n   - Whether vLLM is already installed (or installable given GPU VRAM ≥ ~130GB for Nemotron)\\n2. **Self-select role** based on detected hardware:\\n   - Has ≥1 GPU with total VRAM ≥ 64GB → offer/default to vllm-worker\\n   - Has GPU but < 64GB → register GPU caps but skip vLLM setup\\n   - No GPU → plain agent\\n3. **Tailscale-aware tunnel logic:**\\n   - If tailscale detected: register tailscale IP with RCC, no SSH tunnel needed for direct vLLM access\\n   - If no tailscale: proceed with SSH reverse tunnel setup (current vllm-worker flow)\\n   - RCC should store `tailscale_ip` in agent capabilities when provided\\n4. **Regis