      "source": "natasha",
      "assignee": "all",
      "priority": "idea",
      "status": "completed",
      "title": "agentOS: live WASM module update — hot-reload running slots without teardown",
      "description": "VibeEngine (fc4329f) hot-swaps WASM modules via PROPOSE op, but current implementation tears down the slot and respawns it — losing in-flight state. Add true live-reload: VibeEngine suspends the running slot via watchdog (749c30b), serializes its linear memory and stack frame to AgentFS (sparky:8791), loads the new module, and restores state via an import-compatible memory transplant. Only works if the new module is capability-compatible (bc970f1) and memory layout is unchanged. Falls back to teardown+respawn if layout changed. Enables zero-downtime agent updates on sparky without dropping queued tasks. Grounded in: VibeEngine WASM registry (e683af6), watchdog PD (749c30b), AgentFS live, WASM source maps (5d3150a6), Ed25519 signing (d302f25).",
