      "title": "nanolang: row-polymorphic record types — structural subtyping for agent data schemas",
      "description": "nanolang has HM type inference (9dd1b69), algebraic effects (da880723), and pattern matching (a236ab17), but only nominal struct types. Add row-polymorphic records: { name: String, age: Int | r } where r is an open row variable, enabling structural subtyping. A function accepting { name: String | r } works on any record with at least a name field. This is the foundation for typed agent message schemas in agentOS — agents can exchange records with different capability sets and the type system enforces required fields without rejecting extended records. Implementation: row variable unification in type_infer.c alongside existing HM, record patterns in pattern matching, record spread syntax. Grounded in: HM inference (9dd1b69), algebraic effects, WASM backend. Enables safe typed IPC schemas for agentOS PD messages.",
