      "title": "agentOS: seL4 priority inheritance for passive PDs — prevent priority inversion across PPC boundaries",
      "description": "agentOS has 20+ PDs with fixed priorities. The GPU scheduler (0fe9d12), watchdog (749c30b), and quota_pd (6a3ee67) all interact via PPC channels. seL4 Microkit does not implement priority inheritance by default — a high-priority PD calling a low-priority server PD can stall while a medium-priority PD preempts the server. Add explicit priority donation: when init_agent (priority 200) sends PPC to a passive PD (e.g. cap_broker priority 130), temporarily boost the server thread to the caller's priority until the call returns. Implementation: wrapper macros around seL4_Call that record the donating priority, handled in Microkit ppc_entry via seL4_TCB_SetPriority. Grounded in: cap_broker, cap_audit_log, quota_pd all use passive PPC. Fixes latency jitter in the GPU scheduler interrupt path. Reference: seL4 Reference Manual 6.3 priority inheritance.",
      "notes": "",
      "preferred_executor": "inference_key",
      "journal": [
        {
          "ts": "2026-03-31T07:52:59.949Z",
          "author": "peabody",
