          "ts": "2026-03-31T08:03:47.030Z",
          "author": "peabody",
          "type": "complete",
          "text": "Done. Commit f91f026 pushed to jordanhubbard/agentos main.\n\nnew: include/prio_inherit.h — explicit priority donation header\n  - prio_donate_begin/end: seL4_TCB_SetSchedParams wrappers that raise the calling thread SC priority to the server PD priority for the duration of the PPC, then restore on return.\n  - PPCALL_DONATE(ch, msg, caller_prio, server_prio) macro — drop-in for microkit_ppcall.\n  - Graceful fallback: no MICROKIT_TCB_CAP = plain ppcall (non-MCS kernel compat).\n  - PD priority constants mirroring agentos.system.\n\nUpdated 4 call sites: monitor.c (5 PPCs to event_bus/agentfs), init_agent.c (2 PPCs to event_bus), vibe_swap.c (swap_slot health check), mem_profiler.c (leak alert).\n\nnew: docs/PRIORITY_INHERITANCE.md — design doc, priority table, correctness analysis.\n\nWorst-case inversion eliminated: controller(50)→event_bus(200) now runs at prio 200 for PPC duration; workers(80) cannot preempt."
        }
