      "title": "nanolang: generational GC — upgrade from refcount to tri-color mark-sweep for cycle collection",
      "description": "nanolang has a reference-counting GC (47ef46f4, 256KB bump-pointer heap). Reference counting cannot collect cycles — mutually referencing closures in async coroutine continuations (67a3cc2, dudley) will leak. Add a tri-color mark-sweep collector as a secondary phase: during GC pause, trace roots from the stack frame and mark reachable objects; sweep unreachable objects with cycle detection. Maintain refcount as the fast path (immediate reclamation on RC=0), use mark-sweep only for the cycle detection phase. Grounded in: refcount_gc.h (47ef46f4), coroutine runtime (dudley), async/await CPS (67a3cc2), algebraic effects (da880723). Enables safe long-running agentOS WASM slots with complex closure graphs without memory leaks. Reference: Bacon-Rajan cycle detection (PLDI 2001).",
