      "title": "agentOS: inter-PD capability attenuation — allow PDs to sub-delegate attenuated caps to child PDs",
      "description": "agentOS has cap_broker (runtime grants), distributed cap revocation (64a6b27), cap_audit_log (1cfffeb), and net_isolator ACL enforcement (2489ef3). Current model: only init_agent and cap_broker can grant capabilities — no PD can sub-delegate. Add capability attenuation: a PD holding a capability can delegate a strictly reduced subset to a child PD it spawns, with cap_broker validating the attenuation chain (child rights ⊆ parent rights). Example: mesh_agent holding net_svc can delegate a net_svc cap restricted to one hostname range to a worker sub-agent, without root involvement. Revocation propagates up the chain (revoking parent revokes all attenuated children). Grounded in: cap_broker, seL4 capability model (seL4 Reference Manual 3.1 access rights), distributed revocation (64a6b27), net_isolator ACL (2489ef3), cap attestation (927564a). Enables hierarchical agent trust for multi-tenant GPU workloads on sparky without granting every agent root-level capabilities. Reference: capability attenuation in EROS/Coyotos capability OS.",
